    "contents" : "---\ntitle: \"Graded Novelty Enoding Task - Stimulus pool analysis\"\noutput: html_document\n---\n```{r  include=FALSE}\nsource(\"difference_innumbers.R\")\n\nlibrary(ez)\nlibrary(ggplot2)\nlibrary(emmeans)\nlibrary(DescTools)\nlibrary(stats)\nlibrary(afex)\nlibrary(effsize)\n```\n\n# The metrics\n\n### Differences between the prototypes\n\n```{r  eval = TRUE, warning=FALSE, echo=FALSE}\n\ndifferences <- c()\nfor (i in 1:nrow(prot_arr)){\n  comp_p_arr <- prot_arr[pict != prot_arr$pict[i]]\n  comp_p_col <- prot_col[pict != prot_col$pict[i]]\n  comp_p_sha <- prot_sha[pict != prot_sha$pict[i]]\n  for (j in 1:nrow(comp_p_arr)){\n    arrdiff <- prot_arr[i] - comp_p_arr[j]\n    ad <- table(arrdiff[,arrdiff != 0])[\"TRUE\"][[1]]\n    if (is.na(ad)){ad <- 0}\n    ###\n    coldiff <- prot_col[i] - comp_p_col[j]\n    cd <- table(coldiff[,coldiff != 0])[\"TRUE\"][[1]]\n    if (is.na(cd)){cd <- 0}\n    ###\n    shadiff <- prot_sha[i] - comp_p_sha[j]\n    sd <- table(shadiff[,shadiff != 0])[\"TRUE\"][[1]]\n    if (is.na(sd)){sd <- 0}\n    ###\n    diffsum <- ad + cd + sd\n    differences <- c(differences,diffsum)\n  }\n}\n\nprint(mean(differences))\n\n```\n\n### Difference from corresponding familiar picture\nAll pictures are compared to a familiar. The number of differences between the three vectors of the pictures yields a difference score.\n\n```{r  eval = TRUE, warning=FALSE, echo=FALSE}\nggplot(difftoprot, aes(x=type, y=DTF, color=type))+\n  geom_jitter(width=0.2, alpha=0.8) +\n  stat_summary(geom = \"errorbar\", fun.data = mean_se, width = 0.2) +\n  stat_summary(geom = \"point\",fun.y = \"mean\",col = \"black\",size = 2,shape = 16) +\n  stat_summary(fun.y=mean, colour=\"black\", geom=\"text\", show.legend = FALSE, \n               vjust=-3.0, aes( label=round(..y.., digits=3))) +\n  theme(legend.position = \"none\") +\n  ylab(\"Difference\")\n\n\n```\n\n\n\n### Mean difference from all prototypes\nWe calculate the difference from all prototypes and take the mean for each picture in the set.\n\n```{r  eval = TRUE, warning=FALSE, echo=FALSE}\nggplot(difftoprots[type != \"\",], aes(x=type, y=DTAF, color=type))+\n  geom_jitter(width=0.2, alpha=0.8) +\n  stat_summary(geom = \"errorbar\", fun.data = mean_se, width = 0.2) +\n  stat_summary(geom = \"point\",fun.y = \"mean\",col = \"black\",size = 2,shape = 16) +\n  stat_summary(fun.y=mean, colour=\"black\", geom=\"text\", show.legend = FALSE, \n               vjust=-3.0, aes( label=round(..y.., digits=3))) +\n  theme(legend.position = \"none\") + \n  ylab(\"Difference\")\n```\n\n### Mean difference from all other pictures in the same category\nWe calculate the differences between each pair of pictures and then take the mean of these differences (19 comparisons per stim).\n\n```{r  eval = TRUE, warning=FALSE, echo=FALSE}\nggplot(diffinnovs[type != \"\",], aes(x=type, y=DTAN, color=type))+\n  geom_jitter(width=0.2, alpha=0.8) +\n  stat_summary(geom = \"errorbar\", fun.data = mean_se, width = 0.2) +\n  stat_summary(geom = \"point\",fun.y = \"mean\",col = \"black\",size = 2,shape = 16) +\n  stat_summary(fun.y=mean, colour=\"black\", geom=\"text\", show.legend = FALSE, \n               vjust=-3.0, aes( label=round(..y.., digits=3))) +\n  theme(legend.position = \"none\") + \n  ylab(\"Difference\")\n```\n\n### Mean difference from all other pictures in the same category per study/test phase\nWe calculate the differences between each pair of pictures and then take the mean of these differences (9 comparisons per stim).\n\n```{r  eval = TRUE, warning=FALSE, echo=FALSE}\nggplot(diffinnovs2[type != \"\",], aes(x=type, y=DTN_byPhase, color=type))+\n  geom_jitter(width=0.2, alpha=0.8) +\n  stat_summary(geom = \"errorbar\", fun.data = mean_se, width = 0.2) +\n  stat_summary(geom = \"point\",fun.y = \"mean\",col = \"black\",size = 2,shape = 16) +\n  stat_summary(fun.y=mean, colour=\"black\", geom=\"text\", show.legend = FALSE, \n               vjust=-3.0, aes( label=round(..y.., digits=3))) +\n  theme(legend.position = \"none\") + \n  ylab(\"Difference\") + \n  facet_wrap(~phase)\n```\n\n### DTPPm - mean Diff To Previously seen Pictures\nWe compare the current picture to all previously seen pictures (25 in first study trial, 26 in 2nd, and so on ..). We take the mean.\n\n```{r  eval = TRUE, warning=FALSE, echo=FALSE}\n# library(ggforce)\n# \n# lmmdat <- as.data.table(read.csv(\"filtereddata_pilot1_alldiffind.csv\"))\n# for (i in 1:15){\n#   print(ggplot(lmmdat, aes(x=stimpresseq, y=DTPPm))+\n#     geom_jitter(aes(color=type),width=0.2, alpha=0.7) +\n#       geom_line(aes(x=stimpresseq, y =DTPPm), alpha=0.3) +\n#     ylab(\"Difference\") + \n#     facet_wrap_paginate(~ workerId, ncol = 2, nrow = 2, page = i))\n# }\n```",
